It was more about a free society wanting to prevent proliferation of totalitarian regimes.  You cannot realistically say that the only difference between the USSR and the USA was economic.<br>
<br>
If the USSR had just wanted to be communist and mind its own business, we wouldn't really have cared.  It was their imperialism we feared, as we feared eventually they might declare war on us and our freedom would be threatened.  We feared the &quot;domino effect,&quot; even though it never happened really.<br>
<br>
